Procedure.description:
Procedure Purpose: MTG-I Yaw-Flip and SKM
Procedure Version: 18 Responsibility: SYS Last Modified Date: 17.10.2022
Change History:
[CBi 2022/10/17 EUM v. 18.0] Implementation of SATMAN Version 9 - 15/04/2022 - Preliminary FOM06: "Changes / AIM#249754: @P.4: restore NOMINAL Ka Antenna Gain @P.5: replaced step NS SKM to SKM WO after Yaw-Flip. @P.6: FCI operations for restart @P.5/AIM#223175: delete and check RW momenum drift management as applied in N_SAT_I150 SKM NS."
EUM edits: Removals of following steps as per EUM/OPS-MTG/VWG/22/1329528 -P.2.A1 Switch LI to WAIT mode -P.2.A2 FCI Work Plan stop (including wheels APC) -P.2.A3 Set Attenuation MAX on GeoSAR (via N_GSR_I011, PAF)
-P.8 FCI ops after YF -P.9 LI ops after YF -P.10 Restore GeoSAR -removed variable for attenuation
-deleting step P.4.A2 Restore Ka Antenna NOMINAL Gain (N_PDD_0060) as this proc is called by N_PDD_0075 previous step / AR..
-Step P.2. handles now the FDIR Gyro STR Diagnostic disabling (see AR2851 and 5949) via variable Disable_FDIR -reenabling after P.7.A1 Wait for FPM full performance
Note: v.15.0, 16.0, 17.0 were created by MOF for implementation of latest FOM06 SATMAN v.9
OBJECTIVES: This procedures executes the MTG-I Yaw-Flip, from AOCS FPM mode and back to FPM after the manoeuves (one yaw-flip manoeuver and one SKM).
PARAMETERS : ------------------
PAF: ------ @P.3: AOCS Yaw-Flip parameters AOCS_YawFlip_SpringEquinox.xml or AOCS_YawFlip_AutumnEquinox.xml @P.9: LI Calibrations : PAF files for calibrations.
PRECONDITION : --------------------- LI is in WAIT or OPERATIONAL
CONFIRMATION : --------------------- After CALIBRATION, LI goes back to origin Mode (WAIT or OPERATIONAL)
Procedure.title: MTG-I Yaw-Flip and SKM
Procedure.author: bihr_OPRE
Procedure.hierarchy: Child Procedures: Default:NomSysPF::N_SYS_I060 called by steps: P.4.A2.A1 Default:NomSysPF::N_SYS_0060 called by steps: P.4.A2.A2 Default:NomSysPF::N_SYS_I063 called by steps: P.4.A2.B1 Default::N_SYS_0063 called by steps: P.4.A2.B2 Default:NomPDD::N_PDD_0075 called by steps: P.5.A1.B3 MTI1::N_SAT_I150 called by steps: P.6.A1
Procedure.history:
[CBi 2022/10/17 EUM v. 18.0] Implementation of SATMAN Version 9 - 15/04/2022 - Preliminary FOM06: "Changes / AIM#249754: @P.4: restore NOMINAL Ka Antenna Gain @P.5: replaced step NS SKM to SKM WO after Yaw-Flip. @P.6: FCI operations for restart @P.5/AIM#223175: delete and check RW momenum drift management as applied in N_SAT_I150 SKM NS."
EUM edits: Removals of following steps as per EUM/OPS-MTG/VWG/22/1329528 -P.2.A1 Switch LI to WAIT mode -P.2.A2 FCI Work Plan stop (including wheels APC) -P.2.A3 Set Attenuation MAX on GeoSAR (via N_GSR_I011, PAF)
-P.8 FCI ops after YF -P.9 LI ops after YF -P.10 Restore GeoSAR -removed variable for attenuation
-deleting step P.4.A2 Restore Ka Antenna NOMINAL Gain (N_PDD_0060) as this proc is called by N_PDD_0075 previous step / AR..
-Step P.2. handles now the FDIR Gyro STR Diagnostic disabling (see AR2851 and 5949) via variable Disable_FDIR -reenabling after P.7.A1 Wait for FPM full performance
Note: v.15.0, 16.0, 17.0 were created by MOF for implementation of latest FOM06 SATMAN v.9
[CBi 2022/09/13 EUM v. 14.0] Actions from OSV TB J test case 4.7.1: Step P.4.A1 changed check expression to & (and) expression instead of the | (or), Step P.2.A3 replaced wrong check expression PLI_OPERA by GEOSAR check for #P!G99F013X != "OPER_MODE"
[CBi 2022/08/10 EUM v. 13.0] -asserted DATE_TREF to DATE_TREF_H, same for OFFSET, DATE_TREF_YF = 0, DATE_TOFFSET_YF = 0 in step to call procedure N_SYS_0063, P.3.A2.B2, -missing values and default values in call to procedure FCI work plan in step P.8.A2: to get the procedure verified and saved w/o errors, needed to assert safety values, when possible, for arguments in step P.8.A2 FCI work plan (e.g. set date in the past, start time to 0 etc.)
[CBi 2022/07/28 EUM v. 12.0] New load PAF block step P.3.A1, -load PAF, step P.3.A1.A1, -extract argument 'season' from value for Z_COEFF_A0 in step P.3.A1.A2, -added arg Z_COEFF_A0 in procedure arguments -asserted DATE_TREF to DATE_TREF_H, same for OFFSET, DATE_TREF_YF = 0, DATE_TOFFSET_YF = 0 in step to call procedure N_SYS_0060, P.3.A2.A2,
[CBi 2022/06/22 EUM v. 11.0] Wait step P.8 removed (duplication of step P.7.A1) -Repoint Ka Antenna (P.4) - option added to skip in case KA is OFF
[CBi 2022/06/21 EUM v. 10.0] edits: - P.11 log step 'End of procedure' added with label END - P.3.A1.A1 and P.3.A1.B1 load PAF steps removed (in SVT-3 PAF is loaded in mother TB, PAF will be added to children procedure SYS_0060 and SYS_0063 - see RID957 discussion) - Step P.5.A1 'Perform NS SKM' replaced by log step to keep numbering (RID432) - Step P.6.A1 argument 'Enable' associated to procedure call 'Enable RW drift momentum management' - was missing, default was 'Upload equinox torque' ; - P.6.A1 /A2 changed Domain to MTI1 - P.7.A2 GOTO END (For SVT-3 PL will not be configured by this procedure)
[RTi 2022/05/29 EUM v. 9.0] step Pause payload updated as per SAT_I150
[CBi 2022/05/20 EUM v. 8.0] P.3.A1.A3 call to SYS_0060 arguments associated FDS inputs for the DATE_TREF for YF: DATE_TREF_YF = #DVAR!MTI1:D_OBT_S_TREF_YF and DATE_TOFFSET_YF = #DVAR!MTI1:D_OBT_T_OFFSET_YF
[CBi 2022/05/18 EUM v. 7.0] based on SATMAN Version 8 - 01/02/2022 - Delta FOM05 Changes: -All arg set to safety value, times in the past, -DATE_TREF and DATE_TOFFSET added for yaw flip
